title.narrative: RESILIENT COMMUNITIES AGAINST VIOLENCE

description.narrative: Communities with higher rates of violence have acquired competences for the protection of children and adolescents against violence, with a gender perspective., which contributes to Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect (Covid), Violence, Exploitation And Abuse. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 3. By 2021, the country has a better system to protect against violence in its various forms in the selected municipalities and departments

title.narrative: Communities with higher rates of violence have acquired competences for the protection of children and adolescents against violence, with a gender perspective.

description.narrative: Escalation of violence was interrupted in 43 highly vulnerable communities by resolving 3,987 conflicts, in many cases preventing homicides, femicides and other serious crimes, providing support to victims and promoting instead social norms respectful of dignity and human rights. In the framework of the Spotlight Initiative, 232,135 children, 250,382 caregivers and 4,462 community members and authorities in 53 municipalities were equipped with the knowledge to enhance protective factors in their communities, foster resilience, report violence when it occurs, and challenge normative beliefs that justify violence. | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/01/2022
